Yes, let's fix the `__repr__`, thanks for catching that!

About extending the behaviour of `Normalize`, I currently like the way it's implemented because it is very explicit what the parameters are. I'm not sure that the case where the same value is present for all channels is that common (but I might be wrong), and having it explicit might save people from bugs (say they wanted to have channel-wise mean, but by mistake did `torch.mean(imgs)`, which reduces to a single number).

